In his State of the Union address, President Biden addressed various issues, including the ongoing conflict between Russia and Ukraine. He highlighted the strength and determination of the Ukrainian people and emphasized that the United States stands with Ukraine. He discussed the actions the U.S. has taken to hold Russia accountable, including economic sanctions and cutting off Russia's access to technology. He also announced that the U.S. Department of Justice is assembling a task force to go after the crimes of Russian oligarchs. Furthermore, he stated that the U.S. will join its allies in closing off American airspace to all Russian flights and will release oil reserves to help lower gas prices. President Biden also discussed his administration's efforts to combat COVID-19, rebuild the economy, invest in infrastructure, lower costs for families, and address other issues such as gun violence, voting rights, and climate change. He called for unity and expressed optimism about the future of the country.